SIMPLE: repast
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Repast
<hw>Re*past"</hw> <pr>(r?-p?st")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>repast</ets>, F. <ets>repas</ets>, LL. <ets>repastus</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>repascere</ets> to feed again; pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- +
<ets>pascere</ets>, <ets>pastum</ets>, to pasture, feed. See
<er>Pasture</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of taking
food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>From dance to sweet <qex>repast</qex> they turn.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is taken as food; a meal; figuratively,
any refreshment.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Sleep . . . thy best
<xex>repast</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Denham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Go and get me some <qex>repast</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repast</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Repast
<hw>Re*past"</hw>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <def>To supply food to; to
feast; to take food.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Repast</xex>
them with my blood.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He then, also, as before, left arbitrary the dieting and
<qex>repasting</qex> of our minds.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Repaster</ent>⟦br⟧
